caption.p: Essential oil composition (%) of Trachymene incisa subsp. incisa variants.

fn.p: C. type = Compound type; MH = monoterpene hydrocarbon, OM = oxygenated monoterpene, SH = sesquiterpene hydrocarbon, SO = oxygenated sesquiterpene, O = Other; t = traces (<0.1%); KIa and KIb = linear retention index relative to n-alkanes on DB-Wax column or DB-5 column respectively; KI 1 and KI 2= literature linear retention index on DB-Wax column and DB-5 column respectively [48]; T.In. = Trachymene incisa subsp. incisa; I and II = typical glabrous and hairy variant respectively; I.M. = Identification method.
